1
00:00:04,873 --> 00:00:06,964
The Vaiṣṇavas
have this saying,

2
00:00:07,646 --> 00:00:10,314
when they enquire 
from one another,

3
00:00:10,314 --> 00:00:13,905
“How are you?”,
they respond by saying,

4
00:00:14,183 --> 00:00:17,986
“As you keep me.”

5
00:00:18,096 --> 00:00:21,531
“The way you’re seeing me, 
viewing me, observing me,

6
00:00:21,531 --> 00:00:25,000
as I’m kept in your heart:

7
00:00:25,051 --> 00:00:28,281
that’s how I am,
that’s what my position is.”

8
00:00:28,670 --> 00:00:33,065
They’re deferring
to the other Vaiṣṇava.

9
00:00:33,696 --> 00:00:38,951
So Guru Mahārāj
makes the point

10
00:00:38,951 --> 00:00:42,844
that although we think 
the will of Kṛṣṇa is supreme,

11
00:00:43,429 --> 00:00:51,413
the will of the devotee is taken 
as being higher, in a sense,

12
00:00:51,513 --> 00:00:56,395
because of Kṛṣṇa being 
bhakta-vatsala,

13
00:00:56,517 --> 00:01:01,556
being in love 
with His devotees,

14
00:01:01,556 --> 00:01:04,183
has so much love and affection
for His devotees

15
00:01:04,183 --> 00:01:07,431
that what they want,

16
00:01:07,478 --> 00:01:11,645
that will trump 
the will of Kṛṣṇa, even.

17
00:01:12,108 --> 00:01:15,787
So Narottam Ṭhākur 
and all others in the line,

18
00:01:15,797 --> 00:01:23,393
they’re saying, “Āśraya laiyā bhaje, 
kṛṣṇa nāhi tare tyāge …” [Pr: 43.1],

19
00:01:23,978 --> 00:01:26,205
don’t try to go to Kṛṣṇa direct,

20
00:01:26,205 --> 00:01:29,042
but take shelter of His devotee—

21
00:01:29,042 --> 00:01:31,625
then you get Kṛṣṇa automatically,

22
00:01:31,625 --> 00:01:36,887
because of Kṛṣṇa’s slavery 
to His slaves.

